
[1]waif

   WAIF, n. Goods found, of which the owner is not known. These were
   originally such goods as a thief, when pursued, threw away to prevent
   being apprehended. They belong to the king, unless the owner makes
   fresh suit of the felon, takes him and brings him to justice.
